      • setLocationSource

        public static void setLocationSource(IGeolocationSource locationSource)
        Sets the location provider and activates it.

        INRIX has built in geolocation tracking module which starts as soon as SDK gets initialized. If you want to provide your own location source then INRIX geolocation tracker will be disabled and replaced with the one specified via this function. All previously set location sources will be deactivated.

        Parameters:
        locationSource - The location provider.

      • setDriving

        public static void setDriving(boolean isDriving)
        Sets whether the user is currently driving or not.

        When isDriving is true, then the underlying location source will be activated with high accuracy and current location tracking will be started. If you started activity recognition tracking (by calling startActivityRecognition(Context)), this function will be automatically called when the user's current activity changes to "DRIVING".

        Parameters:
        isDriving - true if the user is currently driving; otherwise, false.

      • startActivityRecognition

        public static void startActivityRecognition(android.content.Context context)
        Starts activity recognition tracking. ActivityRecognition helps you to save some battery power by enabling and disabling current location tracking based on your current activity. In other words, if the device does not move, the SDK can turn off GPS or other location tracking to save battery power.
        Parameters:
        context - The Android context, which contains global information about the application environment.
        See Also:
        stopActivityRecognition()

      • stopActivityRecognition

        public static void stopActivityRecognition()
        Stops activity recognition tracking.
        See Also:
        startActivityRecognition(android.content.Context)

      • endTrackingSession

        public static void endTrackingSession()
        Ends the tracking session.

        The method will end tracking in 30 seconds, unless tracking is resumed with resumeTrackingSession(android.content.Context).
